==Old English==
===Etymology===
Cognate with Old Frisian [[with#Old Frisian|with]], Old Saxon [[wiþ#Old Saxon|wiþ]], probably a shortening of a Germanic preposition represented by Old English [[wiþer]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/wɪð/}}

===Preposition===
'''wiþ'''
# [[against]], [[opposite]]
# [[along]], [[towards]]
# [[with]]

===Adverb===
'''wiþ'''
# with it; together; [[therewith]]

